<i>adverb</i>: 흐늘흐늘 [흐늘흐늘], 털털 [털털], 탈탈 [탈탈], 천천히 [천ː천히], 찬찬히 [찬ː찬히], 어슬렁어슬렁 [어슬렁어슬렁], 어물어물 [어물어물], 슬슬 [슬슬], 슬며시 [슬며시], 쉬엄쉬엄 [쉬엄쉬엄], 솔솔 [솔솔], 빌빌 [빌빌], 미적미적 [미정미적], 둥둥 [둥둥], 더디 [더디] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt>흐늘흐늘 [흐늘흐늘]</dt><br>
<dd>1. slowly; swayingly</dd><br>
<dd>힘없이 늘어져 느리게 자꾸 흔들리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of drooping feebly and swaying slowly, repeatedly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. in a state of being spongy; in a state of being pulpy; in a state of being squashy</dd><br>
<dd>물체가 단단하지 못해 자꾸 뭉크러지거나 흔들리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the state of being soft-textured so that it keeps swaying or cannot hold its shape.</dd><br>
<dd>3. leisurely; idly</dd><br>
<dd>멋대로 놀고 지내는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of enjoying one's life freely in a leisurely manner.</dd><br>
<dt>털털 [털털]</dt><br>
<dd>1. tap-tap</dd><br>
<dd>먼지 등을 털기 위해 계속해서 가볍게 두드리는 소리. 또는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something is beaten lightly and repeatedly to be dusted, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>2. completely</dd><br>
<dd>아무것도 남지 않게 모두 털어 내는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing an act of shaking everything off, without anything left.</dd><br>
<dd>3. with a clink</dd><br>
<dd>깨지거나 금이 간 두툼한 그릇 같은 것이 부딪칠 때 나는 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when a broken or cracked, thick container, etc., is hit against something.</dd><br>
<dd>4. ploddingly; slowly</dd><br>
<dd>몸이 피곤하거나 기운이 없어 느린 걸음으로 겨우 걷는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one’s slow and sluggish walk because one is very tired or weak.</dd><br>
<dd>5. completely</dd><br>
<dd>속이 텅 비어 있는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing that something is completely empty.</dd><br>
<dd>6. with a clatter</dd><br>
<dd>낡은 자동차나 탈것 등이 흔들리며 느리게 겨우 달리는 소리. 또는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when an old car, etc., rocks and runs slowly, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dt>탈탈 [탈탈]</dt><br>
<dd>1. tap-tap</dd><br>
<dd>먼지 등을 털기 위해 계속 가볍게 두드리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when something is beaten lightly and repeatedly to be dusted, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>2. completely</dd><br>
<dd>남는 것이 없도록 모조리 털어 내는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing an act of shaking everything off, without anything left.</dd><br>
<dd>3. with a clink</dd><br>
<dd>깨지거나 금이 간 얇은 그릇 등이 부딪칠 때 나는 소리.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when a broken or cracked, thin container, etc., is hit against something.</dd><br>
<dd>4. ploddingly; slowly</dd><br>
<dd>나른한 걸음으로 천천히 걷는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one’s slow and sluggish walk.</dd><br>
<dd>5. with a clatter</dd><br>
<dd>낡은 자동차 등이 흔들리며 느리게 달리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word imitating the sound made when an old car, etc., rocks and runs slowly, or describing such a scene.</dd><br>
<dd>6. completely</dd><br>
<dd>속이 텅 비어 있는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing something that is completely empty.</dd><br>
<dt>천천히 [천ː천히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. slowly</dd><br>
<dd>움직임이나 태도가 느리게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of moving or acting slowly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. slowly</dd><br>
<dd>시간상으로 서두르지 않고 나중에.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of doing something in no hurry.</dd><br>
<dt>찬찬히 [찬ː찬히]</dt><br>
<dd>slowly; unhurriedly</dd><br>
<dd>동작이나 태도가 급하지 않고 조금 느리게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of one's behavior or attitude being slightly slow without haste.</dd><br>
<dt>어슬렁어슬렁 [어슬렁어슬렁]</dt><br>
<dd>slowly; sluggishly</dd><br>
<dd>몸집이 큰 사람이나 동물이 몸을 조금 흔들며 천천히 자꾸 걸어 다니는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of a big sized person or animal constantly walking around slowly while swaying his/her or its body from side to side.</dd><br>
<dt>어물어물 [어물어물]</dt><br>
<dd>1. slowly; sluggishly</dd><br>
<dd>느리게 조금씩 자꾸 움직이는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of constantly moving slowly little by little.</dd><br>
<dd>2. equivocally; hesitantly</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 행동 등을 느리고 분명하지 않게 하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of one's words, actions, etc., being slow and not clear.</dd><br>
<dt>슬슬 [슬슬]</dt><br>
<dd>1. stealthily</dd><br>
<dd>남이 알아차리지 못하게 천천히 조용하게 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of acting slowly and quietly so that others do not know.</dd><br>
<dd>2. imperceptibly; softly</dd><br>
<dd>눈이나 설탕 등이 모르는 사이에 저절로 녹는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing snow, sugar, etc., melting away before one knows.</dd><br>
<dd>3. softly; gently</dd><br>
<dd>세지 않게 만지거나 문지르는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of touching or rubbing something tenderly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. adroitly; gently</dd><br>
<dd>겉으로 드러나지 않게 은근히 설득하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of persuading someone indirectly so that one's intention is not revealed.</dd><br>
<dd>5. gently</dd><br>
<dd>바람이 가볍고 부드럽게 부는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the wind blowing lightly and softly.</dd><br>
<dd>6. gently</dd><br>
<dd>가볍게 눈웃음을 치는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of smiling with one's eyes lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>7. slowly</dd><br>
<dd>서두르지 않고 천천히 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of acting slowly, not hastening.</dd><br>
<dd>8. effortlessly</dd><br>
<dd>힘들이지 않고 쉽게 하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of doing something easily without much effort.</dd><br>
<dt>슬며시 [슬며시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. gently</dd><br>
<dd>남이 알아차리지 못하도록 드러나지 않게 가만히.</dd><br>
<dd>In a gentle manner that someone behaves so that other people will not notice.</dd><br>
<dd>2. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>행동이나 상황이 뚜렷하게 드러나지 않고 천천히.</dd><br>
<dd>In a slow manner that an action or situation is not exposed clearly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. slowly</dd><br>
<dd>속으로 천천히 은밀하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being slow and secretive.</dd><br>
<dt>쉬엄쉬엄 [쉬엄쉬엄]</dt><br>
<dd>1. slowly</dd><br>
<dd>서두르지 않고 천천히 쉬어 가며 길을 가거나 일을 하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of walking or working without making haste, taking frequent rests.</dd><br>
<dd>2. (no equivalent expression)</dd><br>
<dd>비나 바람 등이 잠깐씩 그쳤다가 계속되는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of the rain, wind, etc., stopping for a moment and then falling or blowing again repeatedly.</dd><br>
<dt>솔솔 [솔솔]</dt><br>
<dd>1. smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>물이나 가루 등이 틈이나 구멍으로 조금씩 새어 나오는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing water, powder, etc., coming through a crack or hole little by little.</dd><br>
<dd>2. gently</dd><br>
<dd>바람이 부드럽게 부는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the wind blowing softly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>가는 비나 눈이 잇따라 가볍게 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a fine rain or snow falling lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. fluently; smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 글이 막힘없이 잘 나오거나 써지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of speaking or writing without hesitation.</dd><br>
<dd>5. smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>묶이거나 엉킨 실이나 끈이 쉽게 잘 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a tangled or bound thread or string disentangling easily.</dd><br>
<dd>6. easily</dd><br>
<dd>해결하기 어려운 일이나 문제가 쉽게 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a knotty or difficult problem being solved easily.</dd><br>
<dd>7. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>가볍게 냄새가 나거나 연기가 피어오르는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a smell or smoke rising lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>8. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>재미가 은근히 나는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of feeling interested quietly.</dd><br>
<dd>9. slowly; quietly</dd><br>
<dd>잠에 조금씩 빠지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of falling asleep slowly.</dd><br>
<dt>빌빌 [빌빌]</dt><br>
<dd>1. slowly</dd><br>
<dd>기운 없이 느리게 움직이는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one moving slowly with little energy.</dd><br>
<dd>2. lazily</dd><br>
<dd>하는 일 없이 놀거나 왔다 갔다 하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one not doing anything and strolling here and there.</dd><br>
<dt>미적미적 [미정미적]</dt><br>
<dd>slowly; hesitatingly</dd><br>
<dd>빨리 결정하거나 행동하지 않고 자꾸 망설이거나 꾸물대는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing one hesitating or putting off something, without making a prompt decision or dealing with it.</dd><br>
<dt>둥둥 [둥둥]</dt><br>
<dd>slowly; aimlessly</dd><br>
<dd>물체가 공중이나 물 위에 떠서 움직이는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of an object that is floating in the air or on the water.</dd><br>
<dt>더디 [더디]</dt><br>
<dd>slowly</dd><br>
<dd>느리게. 천천히.</dd><br>
<dd>In a slow manner; at slow speed.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>